  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving Access to Humanitarian Services for Myanmar Refugees and Undocumented Myanmar Nationals in Cox&apos;s Bazar</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project, IOM is aiming at reducing waterborne diseases, food insecurity and impact of natural disasters on Rohingya refugees and host communities in Cox&apos;s Bazar District (Bangladesh), in coordination with its implementing partners. In particular, IOM is providing access to sufficient and safe drinking water and sanitation facilities for both communities, enabling to increase safe hygiene practices. This is completed by implementing sustainable water points and latrines, water supply, non-food items provision, and reduction of malnutrition, among others. To address food insecurity and livelihoods needs, IOM is providing the affected communities with agricultural inputs, equipment, and technical expertise. In addition, IOM is also supporting local disaster management committees as well as students&#x2019; groups and increase their knowledge and communication skills on disaster risk reduction.</narrative>
  </description>
